sent transferred uses of surname forms, whereas in America all three forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."]},{"name":"Albert","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Albert</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gwrgeneu \" Fychan\" ap Gwrgeneu was born about 0730, in Cantref, Breconshire, Wales, his father, Gwrgeneu ap Llewelyn, was 32 and his mother, Dyddgu ferch Philip, was 32. He had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Mrs. Gwrgeneu Fychan ap Gwrgeneu. He died about 0830, in his hometown, at the age of 102, and was buried in Cantref, Breconshire, Wales."},"et":{"Abt 730–Abt 830":"umbes 0730–umbes 0830","0730–0830":"0730–0830","0734–Female":"0734–Surnud","0750–0850":"0750–0850","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","0700–0800":"0700–0800","0700":"0700","0730":"0730","0830":"0830","Abt 750":"umbes 0750","0750":"0750","0850":"0850","Abt 730":"umbes 0730","Abt 800":"umbes 0800","Abt 830":"umbes 0830","0800":"0800","0734":"0734","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","Cantref, Breconshire, Wales,":"Cantref, Breconshire, Wales","Radnor, Radnorshire, Wales":"Old Radnor, Radnorshire, Wales","Cantref, Breconshire, Wales":"Cantref, Breconshire, Wales","Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomeryshire, Wales"},"fi":{"Abt 730–Abt 830":"noin 0730–noin 0830","0730–0830":"0730–0830","0734–Female":"0734–Kuollut","0750–0850":"0750–0850","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","0700–0800":"0700–0800","0700":"0700","0730":"